         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">6/2/83. ¶  ¶ Only a few lines, dear Prof. Tate, to say, that I have critically and carefully examined a Cuscuta, obtained by Mr Chr Giles ¶ Christopher Giles. ¶  ¶ some years ago near Lady Charlotte's...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">83.02.06</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Ralph Tate</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Barr Smith Library, University of Adelaide, SA.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">6/2/83.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Only a few lines, dear Prof. Tate, to say, that I have critically and carefully examined a Cuscuta, obtained by Mr Chr Giles<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Christopher Giles.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>some years ago near Lady Charlotte's Waters,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Charlotte waters, SA.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and find it a 3- or 4-merous var. of C. australis. A similar form is known from S. Europe, not separate from the typical plant as a species; this was well shown by Engelmann.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A specimen was also sent with<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M to G. Engelmann, 7 February<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1883<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 83-02-07a).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The reference is to Engelmann (1859), pp. 492-3.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">You may be quite right as regards the Hypoxides. I took the small one for the true H.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Hypoxis</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>glabella, because RBr. says of it in the prodromus expressly "scapo medio<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">bi</hi>
               </seg>bracteolato".<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>R.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Brown (1810), p. 289.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Hence Schlechtendal in 1846 took the larger plant of Dr Behrs collection from Tanunda as a new species, and named it H. vaginata, and in this way I disposed of both for years, til I thought it was best to unite the two, just as I joined H. pratensis to H hygrometrica.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>Both unifications in B67.12.01, p.96.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>A crucial test for the validity would be the examination of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">ripe seeds</hi>
               </seg>. We have a similar case with Arthropodium minus &amp; A. paniculatum.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>For discussion, see<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>B70.1.01, pp. 66-7.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Arthropodium<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>minus</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Arthropodium<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>paniculatum</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Cuscuta</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Hypoxis<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>glabella</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Hypoxis<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>hygrometrica</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Hypoxis<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>pratensis</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Hypoxis<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>vaginata</p>
         </div>
